&gt;
&gt;&gt; My concurrency knowledge is less than it should be. Could you
provide
&gt;&gt; sample code for this? I assume you meant this:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; class MyTestFixture extends TestCase
&gt;&gt;     setUp:
&gt;&gt;         synchronized (MyTestFixture.class) {
&gt;&gt;             // set up code
&gt;&gt;         }
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     tearDown:
&gt;&gt;         synchronized (MyTestFixture.class) {
&gt;&gt;             // tear down code
&gt;&gt;         }
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;     testX:
&gt;&gt;         synchronized (MyTestFixture.class) {
&gt;&gt;             // test code
&gt;&gt;         }
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Thanks.
&gt;
&gt;Exactly. Since Junit runs each test in an independent thread and runs
the
&gt;setUp() and tearDown() methods in the main thread this ensres that
&gt;everything is synchronized and that tests do not stomp on each other.
&gt;
